# Kurs na LDEK — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS with custom config (brand colors, fonts)
- Supabase for auth, database, realtime
- Framer Motion for animations
- Recharts for data visualization
- Radix UI primitives for accessible components
- Zustand for client state
- ts-fsrs for spaced repetition

## Design System
- Background: #002A27, Cards: #1E3F44 / #1F4F5A
- Gold accent: #C9A84C, Sage interactive: #367368
- Fonts: DM Serif Display (headings), DM Sans (body + all UI text)
- Icons: lucide-react, 20px nav / 16px inline, monoline
- Border radius: 14px cards, 8px buttons, 24px pills

## Conventions
- All UI text in Polish
- Use server components by default, client components only when needed
- Colocate components with their routes when possible
- Use `cn()` helper (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Validate all API inputs with Zod schemas
- Use Supabase RLS — never trust the client
- Animations: subtle, 200-300ms, ease-out. No bouncy/elastic.
- No emoji in UI. Lucide icons only.

## File naming
- Components: PascalCase (TopicCard.tsx)
- Utilities: camelCase (calculateXp.ts)
- Types: types.ts in each feature folder
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE in constants.ts